This paper discusses a method for dynamically clustering records in an RDF data management system, which falls under the category of database management systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of SPARQL, which is a query language for RDF, indicating a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of locality-sensitive hashing (LSH), which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the need for workload-adaptive and self-tuning RDF data management systems, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
